<p>Resembling previous experimental protocols [
 <xref rid="B21-viruses-10-00200" ref-type="bibr">21</xref>], our ABM-simulated infection is initialized by choosing a number of cells at random that are infected with probability 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm27">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msup>
      <mi>p</mi>
      <mi>init</mi>
     </msup>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi>t</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> during the first 17 h of a simulation. Hereby, 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm28">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msup>
      <mi>p</mi>
      <mi>init</mi>
     </msup>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi>t</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is defined by:
 <disp-formula id="FD4-viruses-10-00200">
  <label>(4)</label>
  <math id="mm29">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msup>
      <mi>p</mi>
      <mi>init</mi>
     </msup>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi>t</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>:</mo>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mover accent="true">
      <msub>
       <mi>I</mi>
       <mn>0</mn>
      </msub>
      <mo stretchy="false">^</mo>
     </mover>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <mi>λ</mi>
       <msup>
        <mi>e</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mi>λ</mi>
         <mi>t</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msup>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mn>1</mn>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <msup>
        <mi>e</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mn>17</mn>
         <mi>λ</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msup>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mspace width="0.166667em"/>
     <mspace width="0.166667em"/>
     <mo>,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> with 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm30">
   <mrow>
    <mover accent="true">
     <msub>
      <mi>I</mi>
      <mn>0</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo stretchy="false">^</mo>
    </mover>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> denoting the expected total number of infected cells during initialization, and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm31">
   <mrow>
    <mi>λ</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> the rate at which the inoculum used for infection looses its infectivity. At 17 h post infection, the total extracellular virus concentration is reset to zero, representing the change of media.
</p>
